hpnicfNat.name: hpnicfNat

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfNat.description: This MIB contains objects to manage configuration of NAT. There are no constraints on this MIB.

hpnicfNATClearSessionSlotNo.name: hpnicfNATClearSessionSlotNo
hpnicfNATClearSessionSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board in which administrator wants to clear data of the session. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it. This node only supports 'set' operation. The return value of 'get' operation is meaningless.

hpnicfNATBLConnectHighValue.name: hpnicfNATBLConnectHighValue
hpnicfNATBLConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. If the connection amount exceeds the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection amount is less than the minimal connection amount.

hpnicfNATBLConnectHighRate.name: hpnicfNATBLConnectHighRate
hpnicfNATBLConnectHighRate.description: The maximal connection rate(in second). If the connection rate exceed the value, the IP address will be added into blacklist. The IP address will not be removed from blacklist until the connection rate is less than the minimal connection rate.

hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.name: hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate
hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectHighRate.description: The maximal special connection rate(in second). When administrator wants to control the speed of connection, he can selects the connection speed rate or special connection rate.

hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.name: hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate
hpnicfNATBLSpecialConnectLowRate.description: The minimal special connection rate(in second).

hpnicfNATBLConnectSumEnable.name: hpnicfNATBLConnectSumEnable
hpnicfNATBLConnectSumEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection amount control.

hpnicfNATBLConnectRateEnable.name: hpnicfNATBLConnectRateEnable
hpnicfNATBLConnectRateEnable.description: Enable or disable the connection rate control.

hpnicfNATNPAgingTime.name: hpnicfNATNPAgingTime
hpnicfNATNPAgingTime.description: There are two kinds of aging time in NP. One is fast and the other is slow. Administrator can select one or other. The defalult is fast.

hpnicfNATPoolInfoTable.name: hpnicfNATPoolInfoTable
hpnicfNATPoolInfoTable.description: NAT address pool table : The address in the pool is the IP address in the global network. The pool can span 255 IP addresses.All address pools configured by administrator are recorded in this table.

hpnicfNATPoolInfoEntry.name: hpnicfNATPoolInfoEntry
hpnicfNATPoolInfoEntry.description: The entry of NAT address pool table.

hpnicfNATPoolIdx.name: hpnicfNATPoolIdx
hpnicfNATPoolIdx.description: Index of the address pool: The index uniquely indicates the address pool in the system, and its range is from 1 to 320.

hpnicfNATPoolStartIpAddr.name: hpnicfNATPoolStartIpAddr
hpnicfNATPoolStartIpAddr.description: The start IP address of address pool: It must be less than or equal to the end IP address.

hpnicfNATPoolEndIpAddr.name: hpnicfNATPoolEndIpAddr
hpnicfNATPoolEndIpAddr.description: The end IP address of address pool: It must be more than or equal to the start IP address.

hpnicfNATPoolSlotNo.name: hpnicfNATPoolSlotNo
hpnicfNATPoolSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board to which the address pool is bound. The address translation is processed by this NAT board . The relation between address pool and slotNo is n:1. When the address pool is not bound to the NAT board,the value is 255.

hpnicfNATPoolRefCounter.name: hpnicfNATPoolRefCounter
hpnicfNATPoolRefCounter.description: The counter of reference. A address pool can be associated with more than one ACL and the counter of reference is recorded in this field. When the address pool is not associated with ACL, the value is 0.

hpnicfNATPoolRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATPoolRowStatus
hpnicfNATPoolRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATPoolIdx, hpnicfNATPoolStartIpAddr and hpnicfNATPoolEndIpAddr were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hpnicfNATOutboundTable.name: hpnicfNATOutboundTable
hpnicfNATOutboundTable.description: NAT out bound table: through associating ACL number, address pool with NAT board, administrator can designate which inside IP address can be translated to global IP address in the pool and the translation is processed by which NAT board.

hpnicfNATOutboundEntry.name: hpnicfNATOutboundEntry
hpnicfNATOutboundEntry.description: The entry of NAT out bound table.

hpnicfNATOutboundAclNo.name: hpnicfNATOutboundAclNo
hpnicfNATOutboundAclNo.description: The number of ACL(Access Control List). When the packet accords with the rule in the ACL, its source IP address will be translated to IP address in Address pool.

hpnicfNATOutboundPoolIdx.name: hpnicfNATOutboundPoolIdx
hpnicfNATOutboundPoolIdx.description: The index of address pool in hpnicfNATPoolInfoTable. when administrator doesn't use the address pool and use the IP address of the interface as the address of global network, the value is 2147483647.

hpnicfNATOutboundIsNoPat.name: hpnicfNATOutboundIsNoPat
hpnicfNATOutboundIsNoPat.description: Whether to use no pat manner. The translation of no pat is that the translation doesn't use the port information of packet.

hpnicfNATOutboundSlotNo.name: hpnicfNATOutboundSlotNo
hpnicfNATOutboundSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hpnicfNATOutboundRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATOutboundRowStatus
hpnicfNATOutboundRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATOutboundAclNo or hpnicfNATOutboundAclNo and hpnicfNATOutboundPoolIdx were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hpnicfNATServerTable.name: hpnicfNATServerTable
hpnicfNATServerTable.description: NAT inside Server Table. Administrator can configure server in the private network which can provide service for people in the public network. The translation map is : (InsideIP , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort ) (InsideIP + 1 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 1) (InsideIP + 2 , InsidePort--> GlobalIP, GlobalPort + 2) ... ... ... (InsideIP+n(=InsideIP2),InsidePort--> GlobalIP,GlobalPort+n(=GlobalPort2))

hpnicfNATServerEntry.name: hpnicfNATServerEntry
hpnicfNATServerEntry.description: The entry of NAT inside server table.

hpnicfNATServerProType.name: hpnicfNATServerProType
hpnicfNATServerProType.description: The type of protocol: icmp(1), tcp(6), udp(17) and others.

hpnicfNATServerGlobalIP.name: hpnicfNATServerGlobalIP
hpnicfNATServerGlobalIP.description: The global IP address of Inside Server.

hpnicfNATServerStartGlobalPort.name: hpnicfNATServerStartGlobalPort
hpnicfNATServerStartGlobalPort.description: The start global port of Inside Server. When the port need not be configured, the value is 0.

hpnicfNATServerEndGlobalPort.name: hpnicfNATServerEndGlobalPort
hpnicfNATServerEndGlobalPort.description: The end global port of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0. If the value is not zero, the value of (GlobalPort2-GlobalPort) must be equal to (InsideIP2 - InsideIP).

hpnicfNATServerStartInsideIP.name: hpnicfNATServerStartInsideIP
hpnicfNATServerStartInsideIP.description: The start private IP address of Inside Server.

hpnicfNATServerEndInsideIP.name: hpnicfNATServerEndInsideIP
hpnicfNATServerEndInsideIP.description: The end private IP address of Inside Server. When administrator doesn't configure a series of inside server, the value is 0.0.0.0.

hpnicfNATServerInsidePort.name: hpnicfNATServerInsidePort
hpnicfNATServerInsidePort.description: The private port of Inside Server.

hpnicfNATServerSlotNo.name: hpnicfNATServerSlotNo
hpnicfNATServerSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hpnicfNATServerAclNumber.name: hpnicfNATServerAclNumber
hpnicfNATServerAclNumber.description: Number of basic or advanced acl.

hpnicfNATServerRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATServerRowStatus
hpnicfNATServerRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATServerProType, hpnicfNATServerGlobalIP, hpnicfNATServerGlobalPort and hpnicfNATServerInsideIP were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hpnicfNATTimeOutTable.name: hpnicfNATTimeOutTable
hpnicfNATTimeOutTable.description: NAT Time out Table. When a connection is established, if there are not any actives in this connection between the time, it will be disconnected.

hpnicfNATTimeOutEntry.name: hpnicfNATTimeOutEntry
hpnicfNATTimeOutEntry.description: The entry of NAT Time out Table.

hpnicfNATBLEnableTable.name: hpnicfNATBLEnableTable
hpnicfNATBLEnableTable.description: NAT blacklist function Enable Table. In this table, administrator can decide whether to start the function of blacklist in the NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the number of NAT board is 256.

hpnicfNATBLEnableEntry.name: hpnicfNATBLEnableEntry
hpnicfNATBLEnableEntry.description: The entry of NAT blacklist Enable Table.

hpnicfNATBLEnableSlotNo.name: hpnicfNATBLEnableSlotNo
hpnicfNATBLEnableSlotNo.description: The number of NAT board. When the function of blacklist can't be set for a NAT board, the value is 255.

hpnicfNATBLEnable.name: hpnicfNATBLEnable
hpnicfNATBLEnable.description: Start or stop of function of balcklist.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaTable.description: The table of connection control of special IP address. In this table, administrator can decide to adopt which manner to control the connection which IP address is the special IP address.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaEntry.description: The entry of the table of connection control of special IP address.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitParaIP.description: The special IP address. The IP is private IP address.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectHighValue.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectHighValue
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectHighValue.description: The maximal connection amount. It must be more than the minimal connection amount.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLowValue.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLowValue
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLowValue.description: The minimal connection amount. It must be less than the maximal connection amount.

hpnicfNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.name: hpnicfNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate
hpnicfNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate.description: Whether to use the special connection rate control.

hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus
hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLimitRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATBLIPConnectHighValue, hpnicfNATBLIPConnectLowValue and hpnicfNATBLIPUseSpecialConnectRate were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hpnicfNATBLManagerTable.name: hpnicfNATBLManagerTable
hpnicfNATBLManagerTable.description: The management table of blacklist. The table doesn't support 'getnext' operation.

hpnicfNATBLManagerEntry.name: hpnicfNATBLManagerEntry
hpnicfNATBLManagerEntry.description: The entry of management table of blacklist.

hpnicfNATBLIpAdress.name: hpnicfNATBLIpAdress
hpnicfNATBLIpAdress.description: The IP address of entry of blacklist.

hpnicfNATBLConSpd.name: hpnicfNATBLConSpd
hpnicfNATBLConSpd.description: The state of connection rate: red(1) : the connection rate is above the upper limit. yellow(2): the connection rate is between the upper and lower limit. green(3) : the conneciton rate is below the lower limit.

hpnicfNATStatTable.name: hpnicfNATStatTable
hpnicfNATStatTable.description: The statistics information table of NAT module.

hpnicfNATStatEntry.name: hpnicfNATStatEntry
hpnicfNATStatEntry.description: The entry of statistics information table of NAT module.

hpnicfNATStatNATBoardNo.name: hpnicfNATStatNATBoardNo
hpnicfNATStatNATBoardNo.description: The number of NAT board. In router, the value is 255 because no NAT board in it.

hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCount.name: hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCount
hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCount.description: Active PAT session count In software.

hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.name: hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCountInNP
hpnicfNATStatActiveTblCountInNP.description: Active PAT session count In NP.

hpnicfNATStatNumOfUsedPort.name: hpnicfNATStatNumOfUsedPort
hpnicfNATStatNumOfUsedPort.description: The number of used port in NP.

hpnicfNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.name: hpnicfNATStatNumOfGoodPkt
hpnicfNATStatNumOfGoodPkt.description: The number of good packet in NP.

hpnicfNATStatNumOfBadPkt.name: hpnicfNATStatNumOfBadPkt
hpnicfNATStatNumOfBadPkt.description: The number of bad packet in NP.

hpnicfNATSequenceSessionCount.name: hpnicfNATSequenceSessionCount
hpnicfNATSequenceSessionCount.description: Active session table count hash by private IP.

hpnicfNATSessionTable.name: hpnicfNATSessionTable
hpnicfNATSessionTable.description: The nat session information table. There is the address translation information in the table. The sketch map of connection is pc1(private Net)------------------>NAT Device ------------------>Server(public Net) InsideIP, InsidePort---->translating to GlobalIP, GlobalPort------>PeerIP, PeerPort.

hpnicfNATSessionEntry.name: hpnicfNATSessionEntry
hpnicfNATSessionEntry.description: The entry of session information table.

hpnicfNATSessionHashNumber.name: hpnicfNATSessionHashNumber
hpnicfNATSessionHashNumber.description: The row number of the hash table.

hpnicfNATStaticRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATStaticRowStatus
hpnicfNATStaticRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATStaticInsideIp and hpnicfNATStaticGlobalIp were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.

hpnicfNATStaticEnableTable.name: hpnicfNATStaticEnableTable
hpnicfNATStaticEnableTable.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

hpnicfNATStaticEnableEntry.name: hpnicfNATStaticEnableEntry
hpnicfNATStaticEnableEntry.description: Active the static Nat on interface.

hpnicfNATStaticEnable.name: hpnicfNATStaticEnable
hpnicfNATStaticEnable.description: Enable/disable the static Nat on the interface(hpnicfNatStaticEnableIfIndex). disable (0) enable (1)

hpnicfNATDnsMapTable.name: hpnicfNATDnsMapTable
hpnicfNATDnsMapTable.description: This table is used to set mapping of DNS.

hpnicfNATDnsMapProtocolType.name: hpnicfNATDnsMapProtocolType
hpnicfNATDnsMapProtocolType.description: TCP Transmission Control Protocol. UDP User Datagram Protocol.

hpnicfNATDnsMapLastUseTime.name: hpnicfNATDnsMapLastUseTime
hpnicfNATDnsMapLastUseTime.description: Its value is the time that the device uses from startup to last use 'Dns Map'record. If the value is 0,the device never use this record.

hpnicfNATDnsMapRowStatus.name: hpnicfNATDnsMapRowStatus
hpnicfNATDnsMapRowStatus.description: Only support 'destroy' and 'createAndGo'. If hpnicfNATDnsMapDomainName, hpnicfNATDnsMapGlobalIp and hpnicfNATDnsMapGlobalPortor hpnicfNATDnsMapDomainName, hpnicfNATDnsMapGlobalIp, hpnicfNATDnsMapGlobalPort and hpnicfNATDnsMapProtocolType were provided correctly, its value is changed 'active'.
